(1995, dir Bryan Singer)

Kevin Spacey rats out a crime lord. I saw this years ago and had never been interested in re-watching as it felt like a movie that would not hold to multiple viewings, and I was right. The cast is still great, with Kevin Spacey and Benicio del Toro both still standing out as the best of the bunch. While the plot felt engaging the first time through I found it fell apart on rewatch, as the story just feels convoluted when you already know how it ends due to its messy internal timeline. A good mystery movie should improve on rewatch when you can more easily pick up the hints to its reveal, but this just feels like misdirection with a twist that‚Äôs barely set up at all. Hard to rate this considering I do think it‚Äôs an interesting watch if you haven‚Äôt seen, but I also don‚Äôt plan to ever watch this again. If you haven‚Äôt seen this (and haven‚Äôt had it spoiled) I think this can be enjoyed but if you are wondering if it holds up it doesn‚Äôt 6/10.";}i:212;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:213;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:3;}i:214;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEuoAwBFXLK";}i:215;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:248:"https://scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/118701923_179698483668283_6121118624949051503_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=107&_nc_ohc=k2opWXxjL2QAX9Irhmw&_nc_tp=18&oh=76cc2a566f21d39b61c623fd655d8ec4&oe=5F7A92EA";}i:216;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:217;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:12985221275;}i:218;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:219;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:220;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:221;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391024415993068201";}i:222;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEuoAnEjXqp";}i:223;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599252343;}i:224;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:261:"FK LASPHALTE SUR LE TOURNAGE DE PANDORE 

